The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, April 21, 2004 				 Tribunal to decide on infotech firms
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, April 20: The finance ministry today said that a prickly issue of infotech companies being allowed to enjoy tax holidays for some of the subsidiaries they had spun off would be decided by tax tribunals.																								A large number of infotech companies, including Wipro, Tata Consultancy and IBM, have been served with tax notices for subsidiaries which they claim should be enjoying tax holidays. Tax claims against Wipro are believed to be around Rs 26 crore. 																								Income tax officials who were assessing these infotech companies have interpreted the law in one way and these firms in another way ... it is now sub-judice and for the tribunal to decide, said revenue secretary Vineeta Rai. 
